Perl OOP:

$oRef->method();

A method can be both an accessor and a mutator

	$oRef->name();       #accessor
	$oRef->name("John"); #mutator

Constructors( Default, Instance, Copy)
	Default  - Empty
	Instance - Certain Paramaters
	Copy     - Clone another object
	
	Can be named anything
	
	Typical usage: $ref = String->new("foo");
	
Ordinary subs get an @_. The first member of @_ for objects is the thing
directly left of the ->

	ref(shift @_)